{This is the companion to Deal 6. The cards are the same except that the 
\Ds and \Cs have been swapped.

Again, WEST has no problem as long as EAST holds at least one Key-card. 
When EAST responds 5\C, (showing one Key-card), WEST can pass. 

That's what happens here.}

